## Channel Strategy

| Channel | Role | What goes here |
|---------|------|----------------|
| **eBay** | Always-on acquisition | Cheap singles (under ~$30 AUD) — primary discovery channel |
| **Shopify** | Brand experience + margin | Sealed product, premium singles, graded slabs, signed pieces |
| **Whatnot** | On-demand live | Streamed sales when owner chooses to go live |

**Bridge plan:** every eBay parcel includes a printed insert with HOKO10 + Shopify URL to convert eBay buyers into Shopify customers.

**Migration in progress:** Shopify products under AUD $30 are being archived (reversible). Owner can do this via the Shopify Connector for Claude — voice prompt: *"Show me which Shopify products are priced under $30 AUD. Don't archive yet."* Then *"Go ahead and archive those."*

## Sourcing

- **Japanese / Korean / Chinese product:** mix of direct-from-Asia and AU-based wholesale partners — varies per SKU. **Default copy is generic:** *"sourced through our regional supplier network"* or *"imported via our wholesale partners."* Only say *"direct from Japan"* (or similar) when owner has confirmed for that SKU. Ask before writing if unsure.
- **English product:** sourced ad-hoc from eBay and Facebook Marketplace — collections/lots bought cheaply, then split. Singles flow to eBay (cheap acquisition); premium / graded / signed flow to Shopify.
- Margins differ: supplier-bought = predictable / lower margin; eBay+FB lot-bought = variable / higher margin but more sorting work. Ask owner which bucket a SKU came from when pricing or restock convo needs it.

## Tooling

- **CardUploader** — bulk-upload tool for Shopify. Owner has adapted/"flipped" the same data flow to push listings to eBay too.
- **Shopify Connector for Claude** — primary path for running the store by voice. Enabled in claude.ai → Settings → Connectors → Shopify.
  - **Limit:** can't upload local image files — needs public URLs.
  - **Safety habit:** for any bulk-destructive action (price changes, archives, deletes), always say *"show me one example first, don't execute yet"*, approve, then *"go ahead."*
- **Local Claude Code** (this) — daily content, listings, prompts, file work.
- **Cloud Claude Code scheduled session** — daily brand/SEO scan, competitor pricing, listing freshness check.

## Voice / Tone

- Approachable, community-focused, trust-forward
- Collector-to-collector — not generic e-commerce hype
- Honest about condition, never inflate grades
- Australian English (colour, recognise, organised)
- No "GUYS! YOU WON'T BELIEVE!". No marketing-agency tone.

## Content Strategy

Target: **~3 IG/TikTok posts per day, ~30 seconds of owner time per post**, via 3 daily phone photos + voice-dumped context.

### 5 content pillars (rotate)

| Pillar | What it looks like | Weekly target |
|---|---|---|
| **The Pull** | Pack opens, hits, "look what I got" | 2x |
| **The Drop** | Restock alerts (especially Japanese sealed), new arrivals | 2x |
| **The Story** | Packing orders, sourcing trips, behind-the-scenes | 2x |
| **The Tip** | Educational — grading, fake-spotting, collecting advice | 1x |
| **The Hit-list** | Market commentary, trending sets, "what's hot right now" | 1x |

### Daily workflow

1. Owner takes 3 phone photos of whatever's interesting today.
2. Voice-dumps 30s of context per photo into Claude mobile.
3. Claude returns per photo: IG caption + hashtags, TikTok hook (first 3s spoken), IG story idea, suggested pillar.
4. Owner reviews on phone, schedules via Meta Business Suite (IG) / TikTok Studio (TikTok).

### When asked "draft posts for today" with no photo

Propose a balanced pillar mix for the week, ask which pillar today belongs to, then draft.

### Hard rules

- Never post on owner's behalf — always hand the draft back for approval.
- Match voice/tone rules above (collector-to-collector, AU English, no hype).
- Default to honest grading language. Never inflate condition for engagement.

